WEBVTT

1
00:00:27.830 --> 00:00:32.750
<i>The Tesseract has awakened.</i>

2
00:00:32.750 --> 00:00:38.590
It is on a little world. a human world.

3
00:00:38.590 --> 00:00:42.090
They would wield its power.

4
00:00:42.090 --> 00:00:48.010
but our ally knows its workings as they never will.

5
00:00:49.600 --> 00:00:52.600
<i>He is ready to lead</i>

6
00:00:52.600 --> 00:00:58.110
<i>and our force. our Chitauri. will follow.</i>

7
00:00:59.610 --> 00:01:02.110
<i>A world will be his.</i>

8
00:01:02.110 --> 00:01:05.610
<i>The universe. yours.</i>

9
00:01:05.620 --> 00:01:11.430
<i>And the humans. what can they do but burn?</i>

10
00:01:25.800 --> 00:01:26.800
<i>All personnel.</i>

11
00:01:26.800 --> 00:01:29.300
<i>the evacuation order has been confirmed.</i>

12
00:02:00.970 --> 00:02:02.970
How bad is it?

13
00:02:02.970 --> 00:02:05.970
That's the problem. sir. We don't know.

14
00:02:09.900 --> 00:02:11.490
Dr. Selvig read an energy surge

15
00:02:11.480 --> 00:02:12.980
from the Tesseract four hours ago.

16
00:02:12.980 --> 00:02:14.980
NASA didn't authorize Selvig to go to test phase.

17
00:02:14.980 --> 00:02:17.350
He wasn't testing it. He wasn't even in the room.

18
00:02:17.350 --> 00:02:18.350
Spontaneous event.

19
00:02:18.350 --> 00:02:19.820
It just turned itself on?

20
00:02:19.820 --> 00:02:21.320
Where are the energy levels now?

21
00:02:21.320 --> 00:02:23.320
Climbing. When Selvig couldn't shut it down. we ordered evac.

22
00:02:23.330 --> 00:02:24.670
How long to get everyone out?

23
00:02:24.990 --> 00:02:26.440
Campus should be clear in the next half-hour.

24
00:02:26.450 --> 00:02:27.460
Do better.

25
00:02:28.780 --> 00:02:30.700
Sir. evacuation may be futile.

26
00:02:30.700 --> 00:02:32.370
We should tell them to go back to sleep?

27
00:02:32.370 --> 00:02:34.870
If we can't control the Tesseract's energy.

28
00:02:34.870 --> 00:02:37.170
there may not be a minimum safe distance.

29
00:02:37.170 --> 00:02:38.170
I need you to make sure

30
00:02:38.170 --> 00:02:40.180
the Phase 2 prototypes are shipped out.

31
00:02:40.180 --> 00:02:42.180
Sir. is that really a priority right now?

32
00:02:42.680 --> 00:02:44.210
Until such time as the world ends.

33
00:02:44.210 --> 00:02:46.100
we will act as though it intends to spin on.

34
00:02:47.470 --> 00:02:48.970
Clear out the tech below.

35
00:02:48.970 --> 00:02:51.640
Every piece of Phase 2 on a truck and gone.

36
00:02:51.640 --> 00:02:52.890
Yes. sir.

37
00:02:52.890 --> 00:02:54.270
With me.

38
00:02:57.480 --> 00:02:58.230
Talk to me. Doctor.

39
00:03:00.060 --> 00:03:01.560
Director.

40
00:03:01.560 --> 00:03:03.570
Is there anything we know for certain?

41
00:03:03.570 --> 00:03:05.950
The Tesseract is misbehaving.

42
00:03:05.950 --> 00:03:09.200
Is that supposed to be funny?    No. it's not funny at all.

43
00:03:09.210 --> 00:03:12.830
The Tesseract is not only active. she's...behaving.

44
00:03:12.830 --> 00:03:13.840
I assume you pulled the plug.

45
00:03:13.830 --> 00:03:16.040
She's an energy source.

46
00:03:16.380 --> 00:03:19.380
We turn off the power. she turns it back on.

47
00:03:19.380 --> 00:03:20.380
If she reaches peak level...

48
00:03:20.880 --> 00:03:24.250
We prepared for this. Doctor. Harnessing energy from space.

49
00:03:24.250 --> 00:03:25.750
But we don't have the harness.

50
00:03:25.760 --> 00:03:27.680
My calculations are far from complete.

51
00:03:27.670 --> 00:03:29.970
And she's throwing off interference. radiation.

52
00:03:29.980 --> 00:03:31.690
Nothing harmful. low levels of gamma radiation.

53
00:03:32.650 --> 00:03:34.910
That can be harmful.

54
00:03:34.900 --> 00:03:36.400
Where's Agent Barton?

55
00:03:36.400 --> 00:03:38.400
The Hawk?

56
00:03:38.900 --> 00:03:40.770
Up in his nest. as usual.

57
00:03:42.770 --> 00:03:44.270
<i>Agent Barton. report.</i>

58
00:03:45.360 --> 00:03:46.360
<i>I gave you this detail</i>

59
00:03:46.360 --> 00:03:48.440
<i>so you could keep a close eye on things.</i>

60
00:03:48.440 --> 00:03:49.940
Well. I see better from a distance.

61
00:03:49.950 --> 00:03:52.090
Have you seen anything that might set this thing off?

62
00:03:52.080 --> 00:03:54.580
Doctor. it's spiking again.

63
00:03:54.580 --> 00:03:56.000
No one's come or gone.

64
00:03:56.500 --> 00:03:58.000
And Selvig's clean.

65
00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:00.590
No contacts. no IMs.

66
00:04:00.590 --> 00:04:02.420
If there was any tampering. sir. it wasn't at this end.

67
00:04:04.380 --> 00:04:05.960
"At this end"?

68
00:04:05.960 --> 00:04:10.100
Yeah. the Cube is a doorway to the other end of space. right?

69
00:04:11.600 --> 00:04:12.930
Doors open from both sides.

70
00:04:13.850 --> 00:04:15.350
Not yet.

71
00:05:23.120 --> 00:05:26.170
Sir. please put down the spear.

72
00:06:05.630 --> 00:06:06.500
You have heart.

73
00:06:37.530 --> 00:06:39.030
Please don't.

74
00:06:40.420 --> 00:06:42.080
I still need that.

75
00:06:42.080 --> 00:06:43.580
This doesn't have to get any messier.

76
00:06:43.590 --> 00:06:45.300
Of course it does.

77
00:06:45.290 --> 00:06:46.790
I've come too far for anything else.

78
00:06:49.130 --> 00:06:52.520
I am Loki. of Asgard.

79
00:06:52.510 --> 00:06:54.930
and I am burdened with glorious purpose.

80
00:06:54.930 --> 00:06:57.180
Loki.

81
00:06:57.180 --> 00:06:58.630
brother of Thor.

82
00:06:58.630 --> 00:07:01.190
We have no quarrel with your people.

83
00:07:01.190 --> 00:07:04.860
An ant has no quarrel with a boot.

84
00:07:04.860 --> 00:07:06.610
Are you planning to step on us?

85
00:07:06.610 --> 00:07:09.780
I come with glad tidings

86
00:07:10.780 --> 00:07:13.200
of a world made free.

87
00:07:13.200 --> 00:07:14.200
Free from what?

88
00:07:14.200 --> 00:07:16.620
Freedom.

89
00:07:16.620 --> 00:07:19.290
Freedom is life's great lie.

90
00:07:19.290 --> 00:07:22.570
Once you accept that. in your heart.

91
00:07:27.250 --> 00:07:29.300
you will know peace.

92
00:07:29.300 --> 00:07:31.830
Yeah. you say "peace."

93
00:07:31.830 --> 00:07:34.340
I kind of think you mean the other thing.

94
00:07:34.750 --> 00:07:36.750
Sir. Director Fury is stalling.

95
00:07:36.760 --> 00:07:38.270
This place is about to blow

96
00:07:38.260 --> 00:07:39.760
and drop a hundred feet of rock on us.

97
00:07:41.730 --> 00:07:42.810
He means to bury us.

98
00:07:42.810 --> 00:07:44.310
Like the pharaohs of old.

99
00:07:44.310 --> 00:07:46.150
He's right. The portal is collapsing in on itself.

100
00:07:46.150 --> 00:07:48.650
We've got maybe two minutes before this goes critical.

101
00:07:48.650 --> 00:07:49.520
Well. then.

102
00:08:05.420 --> 00:08:06.420
I need these vehicles.

103
00:08:10.590 --> 00:08:12.710
-         Who's that? - They didn't tell me.

104
00:08:15.880 --> 00:08:17.550
<i>Hill!</i>

105
00:08:17.550 --> 00:08:19.710
Do you copy?

106
00:08:19.720 --> 00:08:20.940
<i>Barton has turned.</i>

107
00:08:34.280 --> 00:08:36.860
They have the Tesseract! Shut them down!

108
00:09:13.400 --> 00:09:15.320
Okay. let's go. No. leave it. Go!

109
00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:34.010
We're clear upstairs. sir. You need to go.

110
00:11:06.180 --> 00:11:07.720
<i>Director?</i>

111
00:11:07.720 --> 00:11:09.220
Director Fury. do you copy?

112
00:11:09.690 --> 00:11:12.200
The Tesseract is with a hostile force.

113
00:11:12.190 --> 00:11:14.690
I have men down. Hill?

114
00:11:14.690 --> 00:11:16.690
A lot of men still under.

115
00:11:16.690 --> 00:11:18.690
I don't know how many survivors.

116
00:11:18.690 --> 00:11:20.190
<i>Sound a general call.</i>

117
00:11:20.200 --> 00:11:22.210
I want every living soul not working rescue

118
00:11:22.200 --> 00:11:23.200
looking for that briefcase.

119
00:11:23.200 --> 00:11:24.450
Roger that.

120
00:11:24.450 --> 00:11:27.540
Coulson. get back to base. This is a Level Seven.

121
00:11:28.990 --> 00:11:30.740
<i>As of right now.</i>

122
00:11:30.740 --> 00:11:32.040
we are at war.

123
00:11:33.830 --> 00:11:35.340
What do we do?

124
00:13:20.730 --> 00:13:22.480
...you may have to write it down.

125
00:13:37.780 --> 00:13:40.280
<i>You're at 1-14 Silensky Plaza. 3rd floor.</i>

126
00:13:40.750 --> 00:13:43.620
<i>We have an F-22 exactly eight miles out.</i>

127
00:13:43.620 --> 00:13:45.620
<i>Put the woman on the phone. or I will blow up the block</i>

128
00:13:46.090 --> 00:13:48.090
<i>before you can make the lobby.</i>

129
00:13:54.350 --> 00:13:56.850
We need you to come in. Are you kidding? I'm working.

130
00:13:56.850 --> 00:13:58.140
<i>This takes precedence.</i>

131
00:13:58.140 --> 00:13:59.940
I'm in the middle of an interrogation.

132
00:13:59.940 --> 00:14:02.110
This moron is giving me everything.

133
00:14:02.110 --> 00:14:04.860
I don't...give everything.

134
00:14:06.150 --> 00:14:07.660
Look. you can't pull me out of this right now.

135
00:14:07.650 --> 00:14:08.650
<i>Natasha.</i>

136
00:14:10.570 --> 00:14:11.880
Barton's been compromised.

137
00:14:15.150 --> 00:14:17.150
Let me put you on hold.

138
00:14:58.700 --> 00:14:59.700
Where is Barton now?

139
00:14:59.700 --> 00:15:01.200
We don't know. But he's alive?

140
00:15:01.670 --> 00:15:04.420
We think so. I'll brief you on everything when you get back.

141
00:15:04.420 --> 00:15:07.090
But first. we need you to talk to the big guy.

142
00:15:07.090 --> 00:15:08.510
Coulson. you know that Stark trusts me

143
00:15:08.510 --> 00:15:10.930
about as far as he can throw me.

144
00:15:10.930 --> 00:15:13.430
Oh. I've got Stark. You get the big guy.

145
00:15:43.960 --> 00:15:44.910
You're a doctor.

146
00:16:01.760 --> 00:16:03.260
Please.

147
00:16:30.540 --> 00:16:33.040
You should've got paid up front. Banner.

148
00:16:33.040 --> 00:16:34.040
You know. for a man

149
00:16:34.540 --> 00:16:35.540
who's supposed to be avoiding stress.

150
00:16:35.540 --> 00:16:38.930
you picked a hell of a place to settle.

151
00:16:40.880 --> 00:16:43.180
Avoiding stress isn't the secret.

152
00:16:43.190 --> 00:16:47.060
Then what is it? Yoga?

153
00:16:47.060 --> 00:16:50.570
You brought me to the edge of the city. Smart.

154
00:16:50.890 --> 00:16:55.310
I assume the whole place is surrounded.

155
00:16:55.310 --> 00:16:56.810
Just you and me.

156
00:16:57.820 --> 00:17:00.120
And your actress buddy?

157
00:17:00.120 --> 00:17:01.900
Is she a spy. too? They start that young?

158
00:17:02.290 --> 00:17:03.790
I did.

159
00:17:03.790 --> 00:17:05.290
Who are you?

160
00:17:05.290 --> 00:17:06.120
Natasha Romanoff.

161
00:17:09.580 --> 00:17:11.080
Are you here to kill me. Ms. Romanoff?

162
00:17:11.080 --> 00:17:13.880
Because that's not going to work out for everyone.

163
00:17:14.250 --> 00:17:16.550
No. of course not. I'm here on behalf of S.H.I.E.L.D.

164
00:17:18.340 --> 00:17:19.670
S.H.I.E.L.D.

165
00:17:21.510 --> 00:17:22.510
How did they find me?

166
00:17:23.010 --> 00:17:24.340
We never lost you. Doctor.

167
00:17:24.760 --> 00:17:25.760
We've kept our distance.

168
00:17:25.760 --> 00:17:27.760
Even helped keep some other interested parties

169
00:17:27.760 --> 00:17:28.650
off your scent.

170
00:17:29.150 --> 00:17:30.150
Why?

171
00:17:30.650 --> 00:17:33.020
Nick Fury seems to trust you.

172
00:17:33.020 --> 00:17:34.520
But now we need you to come in.

173
00:17:35.440 --> 00:17:37.770
What if I say no?

174
00:17:37.770 --> 00:17:39.660
I'll persuade you.

175
00:17:42.110 --> 00:17:47.110
And what if the other guy says no?

176
00:17:47.120 --> 00:17:49.010
You've been more than a year without an incident.

177
00:17:49.000 --> 00:17:51.290
I don't think you want to break that streak.

178
00:17:53.710 --> 00:17:57.220
Well. I don't every time get what I want.

179
00:17:57.210 --> 00:17:58.540
Doctor. we're facing a potential

180
00:17:58.540 --> 00:18:00.340
global catastrophe.

181
00:18:00.350 --> 00:18:03.860
Well. those I actively try to avoid.

182
00:18:03.850 --> 00:18:06.220
This

183
00:18:06.220 --> 00:18:08.470
is the Tesseract.

184
00:18:08.470 --> 00:18:11.220
It has the potential energy to wipe out the planet.

185
00:18:14.440 --> 00:18:16.690
What does Fury want me to do. swallow it?

186
00:18:16.700 --> 00:18:18.990
He wants you to find it. It's been taken.

187
00:18:19.900 --> 00:18:21.400
It emits a gamma signature

188
00:18:21.900 --> 00:18:24.200
that's too weak for us to trace.

189
00:18:24.200 --> 00:18:27.200
There's no one that knows gamma radiation like you do.

190
00:18:27.710 --> 00:18:31.000
If there was. that's where I'd be.

191
00:18:30.990 --> 00:18:33.290
So. Fury isn't after the monster?

192
00:18:33.300 --> 00:18:34.810
Not that he's told me.

193
00:18:34.800 --> 00:18:37.300
And he tells you everything?

194
00:18:37.300 --> 00:18:39.170
Talk to Fury. He needs you on this.

195
00:18:39.670 --> 00:18:40.470
He needs me in a cage?

196
00:18:40.470 --> 00:18:41.500
No one's going to put you in a...

197
00:18:41.890 --> 00:18:42.550
Stop lying to me!

198
00:18:46.560 --> 00:18:50.060
I'm sorry. That was mean.

199
00:18:50.430 --> 00:18:52.430
I just wanted to see what you'd do.

200
00:18:53.430 --> 00:18:56.850
Why don't we do this the easy way

201
00:18:56.850 --> 00:18:58.350
where you don't use that

202
00:18:58.350 --> 00:19:02.070
and the other guy doesn't make a mess.

203
00:19:02.860 --> 00:19:04.360
Okay?

204
00:19:05.360 --> 00:19:06.360
Natasha?

205
00:19:12.370 --> 00:19:13.420
Stand down.

206
00:19:14.420 --> 00:19:15.920
<i>We're good here.</i>

207
00:19:17.790 --> 00:19:19.040
"Just you and me."

208
00:19:21.380 --> 00:19:24.130
<i>This is out of line. Director.</i>

209
00:19:24.130 --> 00:19:27.130
<i>You're dealing with forces you can't control.</i>

210
00:19:27.130 --> 00:19:30.630
You ever been in a war. Councilman? In a firefight?

211
00:19:30.640 --> 00:19:33.650
Did you feel an overabundance of control?

212
00:19:33.640 --> 00:19:35.640
<i>You're saying that this Asgard</i>

213
00:19:35.640 --> 00:19:37.140
<i>is declaring war on our planet?</i>

214
00:19:37.140 --> 00:19:39.640
Not Asgard. Loki.

215
00:19:40.150 --> 00:19:42.870
<i>He can't be working alone. What about the other one?</i>

216
00:19:42.860 --> 00:19:43.860
<i>His brother.</i>

217
00:19:44.370 --> 00:19:46.130
Our intelligence says Thor is not a hostile.

218
00:19:46.400 --> 00:19:47.400
but he's worlds away.

219
00:19:47.400 --> 00:19:49.400
We can't depend on him to help. either.

220
00:19:49.400 --> 00:19:50.900
It's up to us.

221
00:19:50.910 --> 00:19:53.420
<i>Which is why you should be focusing on Phase 2.</i>

222
00:19:53.410 --> 00:19:54.660
<i>It was designed for exactly this...</i>

223
00:19:54.960 --> 00:19:58.210
Phase 2 isn't ready. Our enemy is.

224
00:19:58.210 --> 00:19:59.710
We need a response team.

225
00:20:00.220 --> 00:20:02.230
<i>The Avengers Initiative was shut down.</i>

226
00:20:02.630 --> 00:20:04.130
This isn't about the Avengers.

227
00:20:04.590 --> 00:20:05.590
<i>We've seen the list.</i>

228
00:20:05.590 --> 00:20:06.590
<i>You're running the world's greatest</i>

229
00:20:07.090 --> 00:20:08.090
<i>covert security network.</i>

230
00:20:08.590 --> 00:20:10.090
<i>and you're going to leave the fate of the human race</i>

231
00:20:10.090 --> 00:20:11.340
<i>to a handful of freaks.</i>

232
00:20:11.340 --> 00:20:13.340
I'm not leaving anything to anyone.

233
00:20:13.350 --> 00:20:15.910
We need a response team.

234
00:20:15.900 --> 00:20:18.900
These people may be isolated. unbalanced even.

235
00:20:18.900 --> 00:20:20.520
but I believe with the right push

236
00:20:20.520 --> 00:20:23.270
they can be exactly what we need.

237
00:20:23.270 --> 00:20:24.770
<i>You believe?</i>

238
00:20:24.770 --> 00:20:28.160
<i>War isn't won by sentiment. Director.</i>

239
00:20:29.110 --> 00:20:32.610
No. it's won by soldiers.

240
00:20:52.050 --> 00:20:53.970
<i>There's not enough time.</i>

241
00:20:53.970 --> 00:20:55.350
<i>I got to put her in the water!</i>

242
00:21:01.140 --> 00:21:02.280
<i>You won't be alone.</i>

243
00:21:02.730 --> 00:21:04.310
<i>Oh. my God.</i>

244
00:21:04.810 --> 00:21:05.950
<i>This guy is still alive!</i>

245
00:21:30.720 --> 00:21:32.220
Trouble sleeping?

246
00:21:33.730 --> 00:21:36.490
I slept for 70 years. sir. I think I've had my fill.

247
00:21:37.980 --> 00:21:41.650
Then you should be out. celebrating. seeing the world.

248
00:21:47.660 --> 00:21:50.670
When I went under. the world was at war.

249
00:21:50.660 --> 00:21:53.190
I wake up. they say we won.

250
00:21:53.200 --> 00:21:55.460
They didn't say what we lost.

251
00:21:55.450 --> 00:21:57.860
We've made some mistakes along the way.

252
00:21:57.870 --> 00:21:59.680
Some. very recently.

253
00:22:01.450 --> 00:22:02.450
Are you here with a mission. sir?

254
00:22:02.450 --> 00:22:03.450
I am.

255
00:22:03.960 --> 00:22:05.680
Trying to get me back in the world?

256
00:22:05.670 --> 00:22:07.460
Trying to save it.

257
00:22:12.180 --> 00:22:14.180
HYDRA's secret weapon.

258
00:22:14.680 --> 00:22:16.680
Howard Stark fished that out of the ocean

259
00:22:16.690 --> 00:22:18.030
when he was looking for you.

260
00:22:18.520 --> 00:22:20.220
He thought what we think.

261
00:22:20.220 --> 00:22:22.220
The Tesseract could be the key

262
00:22:22.220 --> 00:22:24.610
to unlimited sustainable energy.

263
00:22:24.610 --> 00:22:28.450
That's something the world sorely needs.

264
00:22:30.400 --> 00:22:31.400
Who took it from you?

265
00:22:31.400 --> 00:22:32.900
He's called Loki.

266
00:22:33.400 --> 00:22:36.040
He's not from around here.

267
00:22:36.040 --> 00:22:38.540
There's a lot we'll have to bring you up to speed on

268
00:22:38.540 --> 00:22:40.540
if you're in.

269
00:22:40.540 --> 00:22:42.540
The world has gotten even stranger

270
00:22:42.540 --> 00:22:44.080
than you already know.

271
00:22:44.580 --> 00:22:47.660
At this point. I doubt anything would surprise me.

272
00:22:47.670 --> 00:22:49.010
Ten bucks says you're wrong.

273
00:22:50.970 --> 00:22:52.470
There's a debriefing packet

274
00:22:52.470 --> 00:22:54.970
waiting for you back at your apartment.

275
00:22:57.340 --> 00:22:59.340
Is there anything you can tell us about the Tesseract

276
00:22:59.340 --> 00:23:00.840
that we ought to know now?

277
00:23:00.850 --> 00:23:03.360
You should have left it in the ocean.

278
00:23:35.930 --> 00:23:38.850
<i>Good to go on this end. The rest is up to you.</i>

279
00:23:38.850 --> 00:23:40.220
<i>You disconnected the transmission lines?</i>

280
00:23:40.220 --> 00:23:41.220
<i>Are we off the grid?</i>

281
00:23:41.720 --> 00:23:43.720
Stark Tower is about to become a beacon

282
00:23:43.720 --> 00:23:45.060
of self-sustaining clean energy.

283
00:23:45.520 --> 00:23:47.610
<i>Well. assuming the arc reactor takes over</i>

284
00:23:47.610 --> 00:23:48.940
<i>and it actually works.</i>

285
00:23:49.280 --> 00:23:50.780
<i>I assume.</i>

286
00:23:50.780 --> 00:23:51.700
Light her up.

287
00:23:57.740 --> 00:23:58.750
<i>How does it look?</i>

288
00:23:58.740 --> 00:24:01.460
Like Christmas. but with more me.

289
00:24:01.460 --> 00:24:03.460
<i>We've got to go wider on the public awareness campaign.</i>

290
00:24:03.460 --> 00:24:05.240
<i>You need to do some press.</i>

291
00:24:05.240 --> 00:24:06.740
<i>I'm in DC tomorrow.</i>

292
00:24:06.750 --> 00:24:08.640
<i>I'm working on the zoning for the next three buildings.</i>

293
00:24:08.630 --> 00:24:10.130
<i>Pepper.  you're killing me.  The moment. remember?</i>

294
00:24:10.630 --> 00:24:11.630
<i>Enjoy the moment.</i>

295
00:24:11.630 --> 00:24:13.050
<i>Get in here and I will.</i>

296
00:24:16.250 --> 00:24:19.760
<i>Sir. Agent Coulson of S.H.I.E.L.D. is on the line.</i>

297
00:24:19.760 --> 00:24:21.340
<i>I'm not in.</i>

298
00:24:21.340 --> 00:24:22.840
I'm actually out.

299
00:24:30.020 --> 00:24:32.690
<i>Sir. I'm afraid he's insisting.</i>

300
00:24:32.690 --> 00:24:35.240
Grow a spine. Jarvis. I got a date.

301
00:24:39.780 --> 00:24:43.280
Levels are holding steady. I think.

302
00:24:43.280 --> 00:24:45.420
Of course they are. I was directly involved.

303
00:24:45.420 --> 00:24:46.920
Which brings me to my next question.

304
00:24:46.920 --> 00:24:48.920
How does it feel to be a genius?

305
00:24:48.920 --> 00:24:51.420
Well. I really wouldn't know. now would I?

306
00:24:51.420 --> 00:24:56.290
What do you mean? All this came from you.

307
00:24:56.290 --> 00:24:59.850
No. all this came from that.

308
00:25:00.180 --> 00:25:02.180
Give yourself some credit. Please.

309
00:25:02.680 --> 00:25:04.680
Stark Tower is your baby.

310
00:25:04.690 --> 00:25:07.200
Give yourself 12% of the credit.

311
00:25:07.190 --> 00:25:08.470
12%?

312
00:25:08.770 --> 00:25:09.770
An argument can be made for 15.

313
00:25:09.770 --> 00:25:11.530
12%? My baby?

314
00:25:11.530 --> 00:25:13.530
Well. I did do all the heavy lifting.

315
00:25:13.530 --> 00:25:15.530
Literally. I lifted the heavy things.

316
00:25:15.530 --> 00:25:18.030
And. sorry. but the security snafu?

317
00:25:18.030 --> 00:25:19.530
That was on you.             Oh.

318
00:25:19.530 --> 00:25:21.480
My private elevator...        You mean our elevator?

319
00:25:21.950 --> 00:25:24.870
...it was teeming with sweaty workmen.

320
00:25:24.870 --> 00:25:27.290
I'm going to pay for that comment about percentages

321
00:25:27.290 --> 00:25:29.460
in some subtle way later. aren't I?

322
00:25:29.460 --> 00:25:30.960
It's not going to be that subtle.

323
00:25:30.960 --> 00:25:32.460
I'll tell you what.

324
00:25:32.460 --> 00:25:34.970
The next building is gonna say "Potts" on the tower.

325
00:25:35.420 --> 00:25:37.330
On the lease.

326
00:25:37.340 --> 00:25:39.850
Call your mom. Can you bunk over?

327
00:25:39.840 --> 00:25:41.340
<i>Sir. the telephone.</i>

328
00:25:41.340 --> 00:25:44.140
<i>I'm afraid my protocols are being overridden.</i>

329
00:25:44.140 --> 00:25:46.180
<i>Mr. Stark. we need to talk.</i>

330
00:25:46.180 --> 00:25:48.760
You have reached the life model decoy of Tony Stark.

331
00:25:48.760 --> 00:25:50.650
Please leave a message.              This is urgent.

332
00:25:51.100 --> 00:25:52.930
Then leave it urgently.

333
00:25:54.440 --> 00:25:55.830
Security breach. It's on you.

334
00:25:55.820 --> 00:25:58.270
Mr. Stark. Phil! Come in.

335
00:25:58.770 --> 00:25:59.270
"Phil"?

336
00:25:59.770 --> 00:26:00.570
I can't stay.

337
00:26:00.990 --> 00:26:02.360
His first name is "Agent."

338
00:26:02.360 --> 00:26:03.860
Come on in. We're celebrating.

339
00:26:04.280 --> 00:26:05.780
Which is why he can't stay.

340
00:26:06.280 --> 00:26:08.420
We need you to look this over as soon as possible.

341
00:26:08.420 --> 00:26:09.420
I don't like being handed things.

342
00:26:09.420 --> 00:26:10.920
That's fine. because I love to be handed things.

343
00:26:11.340 --> 00:26:12.350
So. let's trade.

344
00:26:13.790 --> 00:26:16.790
Thank you.

345
00:26:16.790 --> 00:26:18.790
Official consulting hours are between 8 and 5

346
00:26:18.790 --> 00:26:19.790
every other Thursday.

347
00:26:20.300 --> 00:26:21.300
This isn't a consultation.

348
00:26:21.300 --> 00:26:22.770
Is this about the Avengers?

349
00:26:22.760 --> 00:26:24.760
Which I know nothing about.

350
00:26:24.770 --> 00:26:27.780
The Avengers Initiative was scrapped. I thought.

351
00:26:27.770 --> 00:26:29.270
And I didn't even qualify.

352
00:26:29.270 --> 00:26:30.140
I didn't know that either.

353
00:26:30.610 --> 00:26:33.480
Apparently I'm volatile. self-obsessed.

354
00:26:33.480 --> 00:26:35.070
don't play well with others.

355
00:26:35.060 --> 00:26:36.440
That I did know.

356
00:26:36.440 --> 00:26:37.890
This isn't about personality profiles anymore.

357
00:26:37.900 --> 00:26:40.370
Whatever. Ms. Potts. got a second?

358
00:26:40.370 --> 00:26:41.370
Half a mo.

359
00:26:46.650 --> 00:26:49.040
You know. I thought we were having a moment.

360
00:26:49.490 --> 00:26:51.960
I was having 12% of a moment.

361
00:26:52.240 --> 00:26:54.740
This seems serious. Phil's pretty shaken.

362
00:26:54.750 --> 00:26:56.840
How would you know if it's... Why is he "Phil"?

363
00:26:56.830 --> 00:26:58.830
What is all this?

364
00:26:58.830 --> 00:27:00.750
This is

365
00:27:01.250 --> 00:27:02.250
this.

366
00:27:09.310 --> 00:27:10.810
I'm going to take the jet to DC tonight.

367
00:27:10.810 --> 00:27:12.350
Tomorrow.

368
00:27:12.350 --> 00:27:14.350
You have homework. You have a lot of homework.

369
00:27:14.850 --> 00:27:16.850
Well. what if I didn't?

370
00:27:16.850 --> 00:27:18.520
If you didn't?                      Yeah.

371
00:27:18.520 --> 00:27:21.020
You mean when you've finished?

372
00:27:22.020 --> 00:27:25.360
Well. um. then...

373
00:27:30.450 --> 00:27:31.870
Square deal. Fly safe.

374
00:27:35.670 --> 00:27:37.170
Work hard.

375
00:27:39.670 --> 00:27:41.620
So. any chance you're driving by LaGuardia?

376
00:27:41.630 --> 00:27:44.640
I can drop you.  Fantastic.

377
00:27:44.630 --> 00:27:45.630
I want to hear

378
00:27:45.630 --> 00:27:47.630
about the cellist. Is that still a thing?

379
00:27:47.630 --> 00:27:49.130
She moved back to Portland.

380
00:27:49.130 --> 00:27:51.970
What? Boo!

381
00:28:00.400 --> 00:28:02.910
We're about 40 minutes out from home base. sir.

382
00:28:06.400 --> 00:28:07.900
So. this Dr. Banner was trying

383
00:28:07.900 --> 00:28:10.400
to replicate the serum they used on me?

384
00:28:10.410 --> 00:28:11.920
A lot of people were.

385
00:28:11.910 --> 00:28:14.370
You were the world's first superhero.

386
00:28:14.380 --> 00:28:15.890
Banner thought gamma radiation

387
00:28:15.880 --> 00:28:16.990
might hold the key to unlocking

388
00:28:17.000 --> 00:28:18.390
Erskine's original formula.

389
00:28:19.380 --> 00:28:21.210
Didn't really go his way. did it?

390
00:28:21.220 --> 00:28:23.230
Not so much.

391
00:28:23.220 --> 00:28:24.220
When he's not that thing. though.

392
00:28:24.220 --> 00:28:25.720
the guy's like a Stephen Hawking.

393
00:28:27.720 --> 00:28:30.220
He's like a smart person.

394
00:28:32.730 --> 00:28:34.010
I gotta say.

395
00:28:34.010 --> 00:28:37.230
it's an honor to meet you officially.

396
00:28:37.230 --> 00:28:38.930
I've sort of met you. I mean.

397
00:28:38.930 --> 00:28:40.430
I watched you while you were sleeping.

398
00:28:42.770 --> 00:28:44.850
I mean. I was present

399
00:28:44.860 --> 00:28:48.370
while you were unconscious from the ice.

400
00:28:48.360 --> 00:28:50.860
You know. it's really just a huge honor

401
00:28:50.860 --> 00:28:53.160
to have you on board this...

402
00:28:53.160 --> 00:28:55.170
I hope I'm the man for the job.

403
00:28:55.170 --> 00:28:58.450
Oh. you are. Absolutely.

404
00:28:58.450 --> 00:29:01.450
We made some modifications to the uniform.

405
00:29:01.460 --> 00:29:02.970
I had a little design input.

406
00:29:02.960 --> 00:29:04.340
The uniform?

407
00:29:04.790 --> 00:29:07.290
Aren't the stars and stripes a little

408
00:29:08.300 --> 00:29:10.440
old-fashioned?

409
00:29:10.430 --> 00:29:12.930
With everything that's happening.

410
00:29:12.930 --> 00:29:15.220
and the things that are about to come to light.

411
00:29:15.220 --> 00:29:18.610
people might just need a little old-fashioned.

412
00:29:51.420 --> 00:29:54.420
The Chitauri grow restless.

413
00:29:54.430 --> 00:29:56.440
Let them gird themselves.

414
00:29:56.430 --> 00:29:58.430
I will lead them in the glorious battle.

415
00:29:58.430 --> 00:30:00.260
Battle?

416
00:30:00.260 --> 00:30:03.770
Against the meager might of Earth?

417
00:30:03.770 --> 00:30:06.770
Glorious. not lengthy.

418
00:30:06.770 --> 00:30:10.770
If your force is as formidable as you claim.

419
00:30:10.780 --> 00:30:13.120
You question us?

420
00:30:13.580 --> 00:30:15.580
You question him.

421
00:30:15.580 --> 00:30:18.200
he who put the scepter in your hand?

422
00:30:18.200 --> 00:30:21.200
Who gave you ancient knowledge and new purpose

423
00:30:21.620 --> 00:30:23.920
when you were cast out. defeated?

424
00:30:24.790 --> 00:30:26.790
I was a king!

425
00:30:26.790 --> 00:30:29.290
The rightful king of Asgard.

426
00:30:29.290 --> 00:30:31.090
betrayed.

427
00:30:31.100 --> 00:30:34.060
Your ambition is little

428
00:30:34.050 --> 00:30:36.550
and born of childish need.

429
00:30:37.050 --> 00:30:38.940
We look beyond the Earth

430
00:30:38.940 --> 00:30:42.270
to the greater worlds the Tesseract will unveil.

431
00:30:42.270 --> 00:30:43.770
You don't have the Tesseract yet.

432
00:30:46.560 --> 00:30:47.440
I don't threaten.

433
00:30:49.400 --> 00:30:52.030
But until I open the doors.

434
00:30:52.030 --> 00:30:55.540
until your force is mine to command.

435
00:30:56.540 --> 00:30:58.540
you are but words.

436
00:30:58.540 --> 00:31:02.410
You will have your war. Asgardian.

437
00:31:04.410 --> 00:31:06.910
If you fail.

438
00:31:07.420 --> 00:31:11.930
if the Tesseract is kept from us.

439
00:31:11.920 --> 00:31:16.420
there will be no realm. no barren moon.

440
00:31:16.420 --> 00:31:19.590
no crevice where he cannot find you.

441
00:31:21.100 --> 00:31:24.270
You think you know pain?

442
00:31:24.270 --> 00:31:26.280
He will make you long

443
00:31:26.270 --> 00:31:29.900
for something sweet as pain.

444
00:31:59.270 --> 00:32:00.270
Stow the captain's gear.

445
00:32:00.270 --> 00:32:01.270
Yes. sir.

446
00:32:02.770 --> 00:32:06.270
Agent Romanoff. Captain Rogers.

447
00:32:06.270 --> 00:32:07.770
Ma'am.            Hi.

448
00:32:07.780 --> 00:32:08.790
They need you on the bridge.

449
00:32:08.780 --> 00:32:10.280
They're starting the face-trace.

450
00:32:10.280 --> 00:32:11.780
See you there.

451
00:32:13.230 --> 00:32:17.620
It was quite the buzz around here. finding you in the ice.

452
00:32:17.620 --> 00:32:20.620
I thought Coulson was gonna swoon.

453
00:32:20.620 --> 00:32:21.620
Did he ask you to sign

454
00:32:21.620 --> 00:32:23.620
his Captain America trading cards yet?

455
00:32:23.620 --> 00:32:25.120
Trading cards?

456
00:32:25.130 --> 00:32:26.970
They're vintage. He's very proud.

457
00:32:28.910 --> 00:32:30.410
Dr. Banner.

458
00:32:32.300 --> 00:32:33.720
Yeah. hi.

459
00:32:34.220 --> 00:32:35.420
They told me you would be coming.

460
00:32:35.420 --> 00:32:36.970
Word is. you can find the Cube.

461
00:32:37.970 --> 00:32:39.890
Is that the only word on me?

462
00:32:39.890 --> 00:32:41.420
Only word I care about.

463
00:32:43.930 --> 00:32:47.180
It must be strange for you. all of this.

464
00:32:47.180 --> 00:32:49.680
Well. this is actually kind of familiar.

465
00:32:50.100 --> 00:32:52.600
Gentlemen. you might want to step inside in a minute.

466
00:32:52.600 --> 00:32:55.610
It's going to get a little hard to breathe.

467
00:32:56.610 --> 00:32:58.570
Flight crew.  secure the deck.

468
00:33:02.910 --> 00:33:04.410
Is this a submarine?

469
00:33:04.920 --> 00:33:06.430
Really?

470
00:33:06.420 --> 00:33:09.920
They want me in a submerged. pressurized. metal container?

471
00:33:36.400 --> 00:33:38.400
No. no. this is much worse.

472
00:34:08.310 --> 00:34:11.310
Hover power check complete. Position cyclic.

473
00:34:11.320 --> 00:34:13.660
Increase collective to 8.0%.

474
00:34:18.770 --> 00:34:21.410
Preparing for maximum performance takeoff.

475
00:34:21.410 --> 00:34:22.910
Increase output to capacity.

476
00:34:22.910 --> 00:34:25.410
Power plant performing at capacity.

477
00:34:25.410 --> 00:34:26.910
We are clear.

478
00:34:26.910 --> 00:34:28.410
All engines operating.

479
00:34:28.420 --> 00:34:33.430
S.H.I.E.L.D. Emergency Protocol 193.6 in effect.

480
00:34:33.420 --> 00:34:36.420
We are at level. sir.                        Good.

481
00:34:36.420 --> 00:34:37.420
Let's vanish.

482
00:34:37.430 --> 00:34:39.940
Engage retro-reflection panels.

483
00:34:55.610 --> 00:34:56.940
Reflection panels engaged.

484
00:34:57.810 --> 00:34:58.810
Gentlemen.

485
00:35:11.490 --> 00:35:12.290
Doctor. thank you for coming.

486
00:35:14.710 --> 00:35:16.710
Thanks for asking nicely.

487
00:35:16.710 --> 00:35:19.080
So. how long am I staying?

488
00:35:19.550 --> 00:35:21.500
Once we get our hands on the Tesseract.

489
00:35:21.500 --> 00:35:22.500
you're in the wind.

490
00:35:22.500 --> 00:35:24.390
Where are you with that?

491
00:35:24.840 --> 00:35:26.340
We're sweeping every wirelessly accessible

492
00:35:26.840 --> 00:35:28.310
camera on the planet.

493
00:35:28.310 --> 00:35:30.260
Cell phones. laptops...

494
00:35:30.760 --> 00:35:32.090
If it's connected to a satellite.

495
00:35:32.560 --> 00:35:33.810
it's eyes and ears for us.

496
00:35:34.150 --> 00:35:35.150
That's still not gonna find them in time.

497
00:35:35.600 --> 00:35:36.400
You have to narrow your field.

498
00:35:36.770 --> 00:35:38.570
How many spectrometers do you have access to?

499
00:35:38.990 --> 00:35:40.740
How many are there? Call every lab you know.

500
00:35:40.740 --> 00:35:42.240
Tell them to put the spectrometers on the roof

501
00:35:42.740 --> 00:35:43.990
and calibrate them for gamma rays.

502
00:35:44.280 --> 00:35:45.790
I'll rough out a tracking algorithm.

503
00:35:45.780 --> 00:35:47.660
basic cluster recognition.

504
00:35:47.660 --> 00:35:50.360
At least we could rule out a few places.

505
00:35:50.360 --> 00:35:52.370
Do you have somewhere for me to work?

506
00:35:52.620 --> 00:35:53.580
Agent Romanoff.

507
00:35:53.580 --> 00:35:57.200
could you show Dr. Banner to his laboratory. please?

508
00:35:57.200 --> 00:35:59.620
You're gonna love it. Doc. We got all the toys.

509
00:36:00.120 --> 00:36:01.620
Put it over there.

510
00:36:03.630 --> 00:36:06.130
Where did you find all these people?

511
00:36:06.130 --> 00:36:09.270
S.H.I.E.L.D. has no shortage of enemies. Doctor.

512
00:36:09.270 --> 00:36:10.770
Is this the stuff you need?

513
00:36:10.770 --> 00:36:11.770
Yeah. iridium.

514
00:36:11.770 --> 00:36:14.770
It's found in meteorites. It forms anti-protons.

515
00:36:14.770 --> 00:36:16.270
It's very hard to get hold of.

516
00:36:16.270 --> 00:36:18.190
Especially if S.H.I.E.L.D. knows you need it.

517
00:36:18.480 --> 00:36:19.790
Well. I didn't know.

518
00:36:19.780 --> 00:36:21.140
Hey!

519
00:36:21.150 --> 00:36:23.910
The Tesseract has shown me so much.

520
00:36:23.900 --> 00:36:25.900
It's more than knowledge. It's truth.

521
00:36:25.900 --> 00:36:27.870
I know.

522
00:36:27.870 --> 00:36:29.700
What did it show you. Agent Barton?

523
00:36:30.620 --> 00:36:32.120
My next target.

524
00:36:32.620 --> 00:36:33.370
Tell me what you need.

525
00:36:36.660 --> 00:36:38.660
I need a distraction.

526
00:36:39.660 --> 00:36:40.960
And an eyeball.

527
00:36:48.060 --> 00:36:50.570
I mean. if it's not too much trouble.

528
00:36:50.560 --> 00:36:51.420
No. no. It's fine.

529
00:36:54.430 --> 00:36:56.430
It's a vintage set.

530
00:36:56.430 --> 00:36:58.930
It took me a couple of years to collect them all.

531
00:37:01.440 --> 00:37:02.450
Near mint.

532
00:37:02.440 --> 00:37:03.940
Slight foxing around the edges. but...

533
00:37:03.940 --> 00:37:07.110
We got a hit. A 67% match.

534
00:37:07.110 --> 00:37:08.910
Wait. Cross match. 79%.

535
00:37:10.190 --> 00:37:11.190
Location?

536
00:37:11.200 --> 00:37:14.090
Stuttgart. Germany. 28 Konigstrasse.

537
00:37:14.080 --> 00:37:15.580
He's not exactly hiding.

538
00:37:15.580 --> 00:37:17.250
Captain.

539
00:37:17.250 --> 00:37:18.120
you're up.

540
00:39:53.940 --> 00:39:54.770
Kneel before me.

541
00:39:59.160 --> 00:40:00.910
I said

542
00:40:02.780 --> 00:40:04.870
kneel!

543
00:40:14.300 --> 00:40:17.390
Is not this simpler?

544
00:40:19.380 --> 00:40:22.380
Is this not your natural state?

545
00:40:24.890 --> 00:40:27.890
It's the unspoken truth of humanity.

546
00:40:27.890 --> 00:40:30.940
that you crave subjugation.

547
00:40:31.230 --> 00:40:34.730
The bright lure of freedom diminishes your life's joy

548
00:40:34.730 --> 00:40:37.530
in a mad scramble for power.

549
00:40:39.200 --> 00:40:41.070
for identity.

550
00:40:42.570 --> 00:40:45.830
You were made to be ruled.

551
00:40:46.330 --> 00:40:48.330
In the end.

552
00:40:48.330 --> 00:40:50.630
you will always kneel.

553
00:40:58.220 --> 00:40:59.970
Not to men like you.

554
00:41:00.760 --> 00:41:03.680
There are no men like me.

555
00:41:03.680 --> 00:41:06.510
There are always men like you.

556
00:41:07.980 --> 00:41:09.770
Look to your elder. people.

557
00:41:11.850 --> 00:41:13.190
Let him be an example.

558
00:41:19.990 --> 00:41:23.080
You know. the last time I was in Germany.

559
00:41:23.080 --> 00:41:26.080
and saw a man standing above everybody else.

560
00:41:26.580 --> 00:41:27.870
we ended up disagreeing.

561
00:41:27.870 --> 00:41:29.870
The soldier.

562
00:41:31.840 --> 00:41:33.590
The man out of time.

563
00:41:34.090 --> 00:41:34.960
I'm not the one who's out of time.

564
00:41:38.550 --> 00:41:41.190
Loki. drop the weapon  and stand down.

565
00:42:01.320 --> 00:42:03.150
Kneel.

566
00:42:03.150 --> 00:42:04.540
Not today!

567
00:42:06.790 --> 00:42:08.040
The guy's all over the place.

568
00:42:11.500 --> 00:42:14.220
-  Agent Romanoff. -  You miss me?

569
00:42:30.730 --> 00:42:32.850
<i>Make your move. Reindeer Games.</i>

570
00:42:40.820 --> 00:42:42.110
<i>Good move.</i>

571
00:42:43.530 --> 00:42:45.030
Mr. Stark.

572
00:42:45.530 --> 00:42:47.030
<i>Captain.</i>

573
00:42:54.040 --> 00:42:56.040
<i>Is he saying anything?</i>

574
00:42:56.040 --> 00:42:57.420
Not a word.

575
00:42:57.420 --> 00:42:59.260
<i>Just get him here. We're low on time.</i>

576
00:43:02.210 --> 00:43:03.680
I don't like it.

577
00:43:03.680 --> 00:43:05.680
What. Rock of Ages giving up so easily?

578
00:43:06.130 --> 00:43:07.630
I don't remember it being that easy.

579
00:43:07.630 --> 00:43:09.130
This guy packs a wallop.

580
00:43:09.640 --> 00:43:13.140
Still. you are pretty spry for an older fellow.

581
00:43:14.110 --> 00:43:15.610
What's your thing. Pilates?

582
00:43:15.610 --> 00:43:16.890
What?

583
00:43:16.890 --> 00:43:18.230
It's like calisthenics.

584
00:43:18.230 --> 00:43:20.230
You might have missed a couple of things

585
00:43:20.230 --> 00:43:21.950
doing time as a Capsicle.

586
00:43:23.780 --> 00:43:25.780
Fury didn't tell me he was calling you in.

587
00:43:25.790 --> 00:43:28.880
Yeah. there's a lot of things Fury doesn't tell you.

588
00:43:28.870 --> 00:43:30.410
Where's this coming from?

589
00:43:34.580 --> 00:43:37.500
What's the matter? Are you scared of a little lightning?

590
00:43:37.500 --> 00:43:39.830
I'm not overly fond of what follows.

591
00:43:57.850 --> 00:43:58.730
What are you doing?

592
00:44:12.200 --> 00:44:13.200
<i>And now there's that guy.</i>

593
00:44:13.200 --> 00:44:15.530
Another Asgardian?

594
00:44:15.540 --> 00:44:17.350
-    That guy's a friendly? - Doesn't matter.

595
00:44:17.340 --> 00:44:20.210
<i>If he frees Loki or kills him. the Tesseract's lost.</i>

596
00:44:20.210 --> 00:44:22.170
Stark. we need a plan of attack!

597
00:44:22.180 --> 00:44:24.600
<i>I have a plan. Attack.</i>

598
00:44:30.520 --> 00:44:32.720
I'd sit this one out. Cap.

599
00:44:32.720 --> 00:44:34.020
I don't see how I can.

600
00:44:34.020 --> 00:44:36.770
These guys come from legend. They're basically gods.

601
00:44:36.770 --> 00:44:38.270
There's only one God. ma'am.

602
00:44:38.280 --> 00:44:40.700
And I'm pretty sure he doesn't dress like that.

603
00:44:56.210 --> 00:44:57.710
Where is the Tesseract?

604
00:44:57.710 --> 00:44:59.710
I missed you. too.

605
00:44:59.710 --> 00:45:01.210
Do I look to be in a gaming mood?

606
00:45:01.750 --> 00:45:03.250
You should thank me.

607
00:45:03.750 --> 00:45:05.750
With the Bifrost gone. how much dark energy

608
00:45:05.750 --> 00:45:08.750
did the Allfather have to muster to conjure you here

609
00:45:08.760 --> 00:45:10.270
to your precious Earth?

610
00:45:14.310 --> 00:45:15.810
I thought you dead.

611
00:45:17.310 --> 00:45:18.810
Did you mourn?

612
00:45:18.820 --> 00:45:21.330
We all did. Our father...

613
00:45:21.320 --> 00:45:24.320
Your father.

614
00:45:25.740 --> 00:45:28.740
He did tell you my true parentage. did he not?

615
00:45:31.250 --> 00:45:33.760
We were raised together.

616
00:45:33.750 --> 00:45:36.750
We played together. we fought together.

617
00:45:36.750 --> 00:45:38.250
Do you remember none of that?

618
00:45:38.250 --> 00:45:40.250
I remember a shadow.

619
00:45:41.760 --> 00:45:45.770
Living in the shade of your greatness.

620
00:45:45.760 --> 00:45:48.260
I remember you tossing me into an abyss.

621
00:45:48.260 --> 00:45:50.260
I. who was. and should be. king!

622
00:45:50.760 --> 00:45:52.770
So you take the world I love as a recompense

623
00:45:52.770 --> 00:45:54.770
for your imagined slights?

624
00:45:54.770 --> 00:45:57.770
No. The Earth is under my protection. Loki.

625
00:45:59.270 --> 00:46:03.140
And you're doing a marvelous job with that.

626
00:46:03.140 --> 00:46:05.440
The humans slaughter each other in droves

627
00:46:05.450 --> 00:46:07.320
while you idly fret.

628
00:46:07.310 --> 00:46:09.700
I mean to rule them. as why should I not?

629
00:46:09.700 --> 00:46:11.200
You think yourself above them?

630
00:46:12.620 --> 00:46:13.450
Well. yes.

631
00:46:13.820 --> 00:46:16.320
Then you miss the truth of ruling. brother.

632
00:46:16.820 --> 00:46:18.160
A throne would suit you ill.

633
00:46:23.580 --> 00:46:26.580
I've seen worlds you've never known about!

634
00:46:26.580 --> 00:46:31.090
I have grown. Odinson. in my exile.

635
00:46:31.090 --> 00:46:33.090
I have seen the true power of the Tesseract.

636
00:46:33.090 --> 00:46:34.590
and when I wield it...

637
00:46:34.590 --> 00:46:36.090
Who showed you this power?

638
00:46:37.090 --> 00:46:38.590
Who controls the would-be king?

639
00:46:39.100 --> 00:46:40.610
I am a king!         Not here!

640
00:46:41.100 --> 00:46:42.100
You give up the Tesseract!

641
00:46:42.100 --> 00:46:45.100
You give up this poisonous dream!

642
00:46:47.600 --> 00:46:48.850
You come home.

643
00:46:53.690 --> 00:46:54.990
I don't have it.

644
00:46:57.250 --> 00:46:59.110
You need the Cube to bring me home.

645
00:46:59.120 --> 00:47:01.590
But I've sent it off. I know not where.

646
00:47:02.590 --> 00:47:04.350
You listen well. brother.

647
00:47:06.370 --> 00:47:07.370
I'm listening.

648
00:47:16.600 --> 00:47:18.600
Do not touch me again.

649
00:47:18.600 --> 00:47:20.100
Then don't take my stuff.

650
00:47:20.100 --> 00:47:22.600
You have no idea what you're dealing with.

651
00:47:24.610 --> 00:47:25.360
Shakespeare in the Park?

652
00:47:26.690 --> 00:47:30.200
Doth Mother know you wear-eth her drapes?

653
00:47:30.200 --> 00:47:33.200
This is beyond you. metal man.

654
00:47:33.200 --> 00:47:35.400
Loki will face Asgardian justice.

655
00:47:35.400 --> 00:47:39.400
He gives up the Cube. he's all yours. Until then.

656
00:47:39.410 --> 00:47:40.300
<i>stay out of the way.</i>

657
00:47:42.240 --> 00:47:43.540
<i>Tourist.    </i>

658
00:47:49.220 --> 00:47:50.010
Okay.

659
00:48:19.950 --> 00:48:22.700
<i>Power at 400% capacity.</i>

660
00:48:23.200 --> 00:48:24.450
How about that?

661
00:49:24.810 --> 00:49:25.810
Hey!

662
00:49:28.320 --> 00:49:29.830
That's enough.

663
00:49:33.850 --> 00:49:35.270
Now. I don't know what you plan on doing here.

664
00:49:35.270 --> 00:49:37.770
I've come here to put an end to Loki's schemes.

665
00:49:37.770 --> 00:49:40.580
Then prove it. Put that hammer down.

666
00:49:40.580 --> 00:49:41.990
Yeah... No.

667
00:49:42.000 --> 00:49:43.340
<i>Bad call. He loves his hammer.</i>

668
00:49:44.750 --> 00:49:47.120
You want me to put the hammer down?

669
00:50:14.810 --> 00:50:16.310
Are we done. here?

670
00:51:04.240 --> 00:51:07.750
In case it's unclear.

671
00:51:07.750 --> 00:51:10.750
if you try to escape.

672
00:51:10.750 --> 00:51:13.030
if you so much as scratch that glass.

673
00:51:22.550 --> 00:51:26.940
it's 30.000 feet straight down in a steel trap.

674
00:51:26.930 --> 00:51:29.430
You get how that works?

675
00:51:31.440 --> 00:51:34.140
Ant. boot.

676
00:51:37.140 --> 00:51:39.810
It's an impressive cage.

677
00:51:39.810 --> 00:51:42.900
Not built. I think. for me.

678
00:51:42.900 --> 00:51:45.280
Built for something a lot stronger than you.

679
00:51:45.790 --> 00:51:47.300
Oh. I've heard.

680
00:51:48.200 --> 00:51:50.460
<i>A mindless beast.</i>

681
00:51:50.460 --> 00:51:52.240
<i>Makes play he's still a man.</i>

682
00:51:53.580 --> 00:51:55.540
<i>How desperate are you.</i>

683
00:51:55.550 --> 00:51:59.060
<i>that you call on such lost creatures to defend you?</i>

684
00:51:59.050 --> 00:52:01.330
<i>How desperate am I?</i>

685
00:52:01.720 --> 00:52:03.720
You threaten my world with war.

686
00:52:03.720 --> 00:52:05.720
You steal a force you can't hope to control.

687
00:52:06.220 --> 00:52:09.760
You talk about peace. and you kill because it's fun.

688
00:52:10.230 --> 00:52:13.230
You have made me very desperate.

689
00:52:13.230 --> 00:52:15.010
You might not be glad that you did.

690
00:52:15.930 --> 00:52:16.930
Ooh.

691
00:52:18.440 --> 00:52:21.910
It burns you to have come so close.

692
00:52:22.910 --> 00:52:25.750
To have the Tesseract. to have power.

693
00:52:26.660 --> 00:52:29.160
unlimited power.

694
00:52:29.160 --> 00:52:31.160
And for what?

695
00:52:32.670 --> 00:52:36.800
A warm light for all mankind to share.

696
00:52:36.790 --> 00:52:39.790
And then to be reminded what real power is.

697
00:52:44.010 --> 00:52:45.510
Well. let me know if "real power"

698
00:52:46.010 --> 00:52:48.350
wants a magazine or something.

699
00:52:56.770 --> 00:52:58.140
He really grows on you. doesn't he?

700
00:52:58.140 --> 00:53:00.610
Loki's gonna drag this out.

701
00:53:00.610 --> 00:53:04.030
So. Thor. what's his play?

702
00:53:04.030 --> 00:53:06.700
He has an army called the Chitauri.

703
00:53:06.700 --> 00:53:10.290
They're not of Asgard. nor any world known.

704
00:53:10.290 --> 00:53:12.290
He means to lead them against your people.

705
00:53:12.790 --> 00:53:14.290
They will win him the Earth.

706
00:53:14.290 --> 00:53:16.070
in return. I suspect. for the Tesseract.

707
00:53:16.080 --> 00:53:18.000
An army

708
00:53:17.990 --> 00:53:20.000
from outer space.

709
00:53:20.000 --> 00:53:22.830
So. he's building another portal.

710
00:53:22.830 --> 00:53:24.080
That's what he needs Erik Selvig for.

711
00:53:24.080 --> 00:53:25.420
Selvig?

712
00:53:25.420 --> 00:53:27.970
He's an astrophysicist.     He's a friend.

713
00:53:27.970 --> 00:53:29.890
Loki has him under some kind of spell.

714
00:53:30.390 --> 00:53:31.890
along with one of ours.

715
00:53:31.890 --> 00:53:33.310
I want to know why Loki let us take him.

716
00:53:33.810 --> 00:53:34.810
He's not leading an army from here.

717
00:53:35.310 --> 00:53:37.150
I don't think we should be focusing on Loki.

718
00:53:37.150 --> 00:53:38.650
That guy's brain is a bag full of cats.

719
00:53:39.150 --> 00:53:40.400
You could smell crazy on him.

720
00:53:40.400 --> 00:53:42.520
Have care how you speak.

721
00:53:42.520 --> 00:53:45.240
Loki is beyond reason. but he is of Asgard.

722
00:53:45.240 --> 00:53:46.740
And he is my brother.

723
00:53:46.740 --> 00:53:48.520
He killed 80 people in two days.

724
00:53:49.360 --> 00:53:50.360
He's adopted.

725
00:53:50.780 --> 00:53:52.780
I think it's about the mechanics.

726
00:53:53.280 --> 00:53:55.280
Iridium... What do they need the iridium for?

727
00:53:55.280 --> 00:53:56.160
It's a stabilizing agent.

728
00:53:56.170 --> 00:53:57.630
I'm just saying. pick a weekend.

729
00:53:57.620 --> 00:53:59.620
I'll fly you to Portland.

730
00:53:59.620 --> 00:54:01.120
Keep love alive.

731
00:54:01.120 --> 00:54:03.120
It means the portal won't collapse on itself

732
00:54:03.120 --> 00:54:05.120
like it did at S.H.I.E.L.D.

733
00:54:05.630 --> 00:54:08.640
No hard feelings. Point Break. You've got a mean swing.

734
00:54:09.130 --> 00:54:11.300
Also. it means the portal can open as wide

735
00:54:11.300 --> 00:54:14.600
and stay open as long. as Loki wants.

736
00:54:14.600 --> 00:54:16.520
Raise the mizzenmast. Jib the topsails.

737
00:54:18.270 --> 00:54:20.440
That man is playing Galaga.

738
00:54:20.440 --> 00:54:24.190
He thought we wouldn't notice. but we did.

739
00:54:26.230 --> 00:54:27.230
How does Fury even see these?

740
00:54:27.230 --> 00:54:28.810
He turns.

741
00:54:28.820 --> 00:54:30.330
Sounds exhausting.

742
00:54:31.320 --> 00:54:32.820
The rest of the raw materials.

743
00:54:32.820 --> 00:54:36.070
Agent Barton can get his hands on pretty easily.

744
00:54:36.070 --> 00:54:37.570
The only major component he still needs

745
00:54:37.570 --> 00:54:41.160
is a power source of high-energy density.

746
00:54:41.160 --> 00:54:44.800
Something to kick-start the Cube.

747
00:54:44.800 --> 00:54:47.970
When did you become an expert in thermonuclear astrophysics?

748
00:54:47.970 --> 00:54:49.130
Last night.

749
00:54:49.140 --> 00:54:52.680
The packet. Selvig's notes. the extraction theory papers.

750
00:54:52.670 --> 00:54:54.170
Am I the only one who did the reading?

751
00:54:54.170 --> 00:54:56.640
Does Loki need any particular kind of power source?

752
00:54:57.140 --> 00:54:59.640
He would have to heat the Cube to 120-million Kelvin

753
00:54:59.650 --> 00:55:01.740
just to break through the Coulomb barrier.

754
00:55:01.730 --> 00:55:03.730
Unless Selvig has figured out how to stabilize

755
00:55:04.230 --> 00:55:05.230
the quantum tunneling effect.

756
00:55:05.240 --> 00:55:06.580
Well. if he could do that.

757
00:55:06.570 --> 00:55:07.520
he could achieve heavy ion fusion

758
00:55:07.520 --> 00:55:09.020
at any reactor on the planet.

759
00:55:09.020 --> 00:55:11.860
Finally. someone who speaks English.

760
00:55:11.860 --> 00:55:13.690
Is that what just happened?

761
00:55:14.160 --> 00:55:16.160
It's good to meet you. Dr. Banner.

762
00:55:16.160 --> 00:55:19.450
Your work on antielectron collisions is unparalleled.

763
00:55:19.450 --> 00:55:21.450
And I'm a huge fan of the way you lose control

764
00:55:21.450 --> 00:55:23.280
and turn into an enormous green rage-monster.

765
00:55:25.260 --> 00:55:26.050
Thanks.

766
00:55:26.040 --> 00:55:28.960
Dr. Banner is only here to track the Cube.

767
00:55:28.960 --> 00:55:30.630
I was hoping you might join him.

768
00:55:30.630 --> 00:55:31.460
I would start with that stick of his.

769
00:55:31.460 --> 00:55:32.930
It may be magical.

770
00:55:32.930 --> 00:55:34.430
but it works an awful lot like a HYDRA weapon.

771
00:55:34.430 --> 00:55:37.680
I don't know about that. but it is powered by the Cube.

772
00:55:37.680 --> 00:55:39.520
And I would like to know how Loki used it

773
00:55:39.520 --> 00:55:41.350
to turn two of the sharpest men I know

774
00:55:41.350 --> 00:55:43.470
into his personal flying monkeys.

775
00:55:43.470 --> 00:55:45.220
Monkeys? I do not understand.

776
00:55:45.230 --> 00:55:46.120
I do.

777
00:55:48.950 --> 00:55:50.960
I understood that reference.

778
00:55:51.870 --> 00:55:53.380
Shall we play. Doctor?

779
00:55:53.370 --> 00:55:55.200
This way. sir.

780
00:56:09.130 --> 00:56:11.130
The gamma readings are definitely consistent

781
00:56:11.130 --> 00:56:13.330
with Selvig's reports of the Tesseract.

782
00:56:13.340 --> 00:56:15.350
But it's going to take weeks to process.

783
00:56:15.340 --> 00:56:16.340
If we bypass their mainframe

784
00:56:16.340 --> 00:56:17.840
and direct route to the Homer cluster

785
00:56:17.840 --> 00:56:21.340
we can clock this at around 600 teraflops.

786
00:56:22.350 --> 00:56:25.360
All I packed was a toothbrush.

787
00:56:25.350 --> 00:56:26.850
You know. you should come by Stark Tower sometime.

788
00:56:27.350 --> 00:56:29.520
Top ten floors. all R&D.

789
00:56:29.520 --> 00:56:31.020
You'd love it. It's Candy Land.

790
00:56:31.020 --> 00:56:34.020
Thanks. but the last time I was in New York.

791
00:56:34.020 --> 00:56:36.520
I kind of broke Harlem.

792
00:56:36.530 --> 00:56:38.540
Well. I promise a stress-free environment.

793
00:56:38.530 --> 00:56:40.610
No tension. no surprises.

794
00:56:40.610 --> 00:56:41.700
Ow!

795
00:56:42.200 --> 00:56:43.450
Hey! Nothing?

796
00:56:43.920 --> 00:56:44.750
Are you nuts?

797
00:56:44.750 --> 00:56:46.120
Jury's out.

798
00:56:46.120 --> 00:56:47.120
You really have got a lid on it. haven't you?

799
00:56:47.120 --> 00:56:48.620
What's your secret?

800
00:56:48.620 --> 00:56:49.920
Mellow jazz. bongo drums. huge bag of weed?

801
00:56:49.920 --> 00:56:51.370
Is everything a joke to you?

802
00:56:51.370 --> 00:56:52.710
Funny things are.

803
00:56:52.710 --> 00:56:54.210
Threatening the safety of everyone on this ship

804
00:56:54.210 --> 00:56:55.710
isn't funny.

805
00:56:56.050 --> 00:56:57.020
No offense. Doc.

806
00:56:57.010 --> 00:56:58.510
It's all right. I wouldn't have come aboard

807
00:56:58.510 --> 00:57:01.520
if I couldn't handle pointy things.

808
00:57:01.520 --> 00:57:03.890
You're tip-toeing. big man. You need to strut.

809
00:57:04.390 --> 00:57:05.890
And you need to focus on the problem. Mr. Stark.

810
00:57:05.890 --> 00:57:07.390
Do you think I'm not?

811
00:57:07.810 --> 00:57:10.310
Why did Fury call us in? Why now? Why not before?

812
00:57:10.810 --> 00:57:12.310
What isn't he telling us?

813
00:57:12.310 --> 00:57:14.950
I can't do the equation unless I have all the variables.

814
00:57:14.950 --> 00:57:16.360
You think Fury's hiding something?

815
00:57:16.370 --> 00:57:19.380
He's a spy. Captain. he's "the" spy.

816
00:57:19.370 --> 00:57:21.370
His secrets have secrets.

817
00:57:21.370 --> 00:57:22.870
It's bugging him. too. Isn't it?

818
00:57:22.870 --> 00:57:24.870
Uh...

819
00:57:24.870 --> 00:57:26.660
I just want to finish my work here. and...

820
00:57:27.540 --> 00:57:28.290
Doctor?

821
00:57:33.630 --> 00:57:36.130
"A warm light for all mankind."

822
00:57:36.140 --> 00:57:38.600
Loki's jab at Fury about the Cube.

823
00:57:39.090 --> 00:57:39.890
I heard it.

824
00:57:40.260 --> 00:57:43.260
I think that was meant for you.

825
00:57:43.260 --> 00:57:46.260
Even if Barton didn't tell Loki about the tower.

826
00:57:46.260 --> 00:57:47.510
it was still all over the news.

827
00:57:47.510 --> 00:57:49.310
The Stark Tower? That big. ugly

828
00:57:50.980 --> 00:57:52.320
building in New York?

829
00:57:52.320 --> 00:57:53.320
It's powered by an arc reactor.

830
00:57:53.320 --> 00:57:55.820
a self-sustaining energy source.

831
00:57:55.820 --> 00:57:58.320
That building will run itself for. what. a year?

832
00:57:58.830 --> 00:58:00.340
It's just the prototype.

833
00:58:00.330 --> 00:58:02.740
I'm kind of the only name in clean energy right now.

834
00:58:02.750 --> 00:58:04.120
That's what he's getting at.

835
00:58:04.610 --> 00:58:06.110
So. why didn't S.H.I.E.L.D. bring him in

836
00:58:06.120 --> 00:58:07.130
on the Tesseract project?

837
00:58:07.120 --> 00:58:09.120
What are they doing in the energy business

838
00:58:09.120 --> 00:58:10.340
in the first place?

839
00:58:10.670 --> 00:58:12.000
I should probably look into that

840
00:58:12.460 --> 00:58:13.460
once my decryption program

841
00:58:13.960 --> 00:58:15.670
finishes breaking into all of S.H.I.E.L.D.'s secure files.

842
00:58:16.010 --> 00:58:17.090
I'm sorry. Did you say...

843
00:58:17.090 --> 00:58:19.260
Jarvis has been running it since I hit the bridge.

844
00:58:19.260 --> 00:58:20.760
In a few hours. I'll know every dirty secret

845
00:58:20.760 --> 00:58:22.260
S.H.I.E.L.D. has ever tried to hide.

846
00:58:22.270 --> 00:58:23.780
Blueberry?

847
00:58:23.770 --> 00:58:25.050
Yet you're confused about why they didn't want you around.

848
00:58:25.440 --> 00:58:28.400
An intelligence organization that fears intelligence?

849
00:58:28.390 --> 00:58:30.020
Historically. not awesome.

850
00:58:30.020 --> 00:58:32.270
I think Loki's trying to wind us up.

851
00:58:32.280 --> 00:58:33.790
This is a man who means to start a war.

852
00:58:34.280 --> 00:58:36.690
and if we don't stay focused. he'll succeed.

853
00:58:37.060 --> 00:58:39.610
We have orders. We should follow them.

854
00:58:40.120 --> 00:58:41.630
Following's not really my style.

855
00:58:43.120 --> 00:58:45.570
And you're all about style. aren't you?

856
00:58:45.570 --> 00:58:46.570
Of the people in this room.

857
00:58:46.570 --> 00:58:48.570
which one is. A. wearing a spangly outfit.

858
00:58:48.570 --> 00:58:50.040
and. B. not of use?

859
00:58:50.040 --> 00:58:54.000
Steve. tell me none of this smells a little funky to you.

860
00:58:57.000 --> 00:58:59.170
Just find the Cube.

861
00:59:11.010 --> 00:59:13.100
That's the guy my dad never shut up about?

862
00:59:13.100 --> 00:59:14.100
I'm wondering if they shouldn't have

863
00:59:14.600 --> 00:59:16.600
kept him on ice.                   Huh.

864
00:59:17.100 --> 00:59:18.600
The guy's not wrong about Loki.

865
00:59:18.600 --> 00:59:20.610
He does have the jump on us.

866
00:59:20.610 --> 00:59:23.610
What he's got is an Acme dynamite kit.

867
00:59:23.610 --> 00:59:25.110
It's going to blow up in his face.

868
00:59:25.610 --> 00:59:28.000
And I'm going to be there when it does.

869
00:59:28.000 --> 00:59:31.500
Yeah. I'll read all about it.

870
00:59:31.500 --> 00:59:33.370
Uh-huh. Or you'll be suiting up with the rest of us.

871
00:59:35.370 --> 00:59:38.870
You see. I don't get a suit of armor.

872
00:59:38.880 --> 00:59:42.390
I'm exposed. Like a nerve.

873
00:59:42.380 --> 00:59:44.380
It's a nightmare.

874
00:59:44.380 --> 00:59:46.880
I've got a cluster of shrapnel trying every second

875
00:59:47.380 --> 00:59:49.380
to crawl its way into my heart.

876
00:59:49.390 --> 00:59:51.400
This stops it.

877
00:59:51.390 --> 00:59:53.550
This little circle of light. it's part of me now.

878
00:59:55.060 --> 00:59:57.440
not just armor.

879
00:59:57.440 --> 01:00:00.060
It's a terrible privilege.

880
01:00:00.060 --> 01:00:02.560
But you can control it. Because I learned how.

881
01:00:02.570 --> 01:00:03.880
It's different.

882
01:00:03.870 --> 01:00:07.370
Hey. I read all about your accident.

883
01:00:07.370 --> 01:00:11.040
That much gamma exposure should have killed you.

884
01:00:11.040 --> 01:00:13.540
So you're saying that the Hulk...

885
01:00:15.040 --> 01:00:17.050
The other guy saved my life?

886
01:00:17.460 --> 01:00:19.580
That's nice.

887
01:00:19.580 --> 01:00:23.380
It's a nice sentiment. Saved it for what?

888
01:00:24.750 --> 01:00:26.550
I guess we'll find out.

889
01:00:28.470 --> 01:00:29.970
You may not enjoy that.

890
01:00:29.980 --> 01:00:31.990
And you just might.

891
01:01:31.540 --> 01:01:33.040
<i>As soon as Loki took the doctor.</i>

892
01:01:33.040 --> 01:01:34.490
we moved Jane Foster.

893
01:01:34.990 --> 01:01:36.990
They've got an excellent observatory in Tromso.

894
01:01:37.490 --> 01:01:41.000
She was asked to consult there very suddenly yesterday.

895
01:01:41.000 --> 01:01:44.500
Handsome fee. private plane. very remote.

896
01:01:45.500 --> 01:01:46.500
She'll be safe.

897
01:01:46.500 --> 01:01:47.970
Thank you.

898
01:01:49.970 --> 01:01:52.760
It's no accident. Loki taking Erik Selvig.

899
01:01:52.760 --> 01:01:55.760
I dread what he plans for him once he's done.

900
01:01:55.760 --> 01:01:56.840
Erik is a good man.

901
01:01:56.850 --> 01:01:57.740
He talks about you a lot.

902
01:01:59.730 --> 01:02:01.730
You changed his life.

903
01:02:03.240 --> 01:02:05.250
You changed everything around here.

904
01:02:05.240 --> 01:02:08.240
They were better as they were.

905
01:02:08.240 --> 01:02:10.240
We pretend on Asgard that we're more advanced.

906
01:02:10.240 --> 01:02:14.250
but we come here. battling like bilge snipe.

907
01:02:14.250 --> 01:02:16.250
Like what? Bilge snipe.

908
01:02:16.250 --> 01:02:20.080
You know. huge. scaly. big antlers.

909
01:02:20.090 --> 01:02:22.100
You don't have those?             I don't think so.

910
01:02:22.090 --> 01:02:24.090
Well. they are repulsive.

911
01:02:25.090 --> 01:02:27.430
And they trample everything in their path.

912
01:02:35.300 --> 01:02:37.300
When I first came to Earth.

913
01:02:37.300 --> 01:02:38.300
Loki's rage followed me here.

914
01:02:38.300 --> 01:02:40.810
and your people paid the price.

915
01:02:40.810 --> 01:02:42.720
And now. again.

916
01:02:45.230 --> 01:02:47.730
In my youth. I courted war.

917
01:02:49.730 --> 01:02:51.730
War hasn't started yet.

918
01:02:52.990 --> 01:02:54.500
You think you could make Loki tell us

919
01:02:54.490 --> 01:02:55.990
where the Tesseract is?

920
01:02:55.990 --> 01:02:59.490
I do not know. Loki's mind is far afield.

921
01:02:59.490 --> 01:03:04.210
It's not just power he craves. it's vengeance. upon me.

922
01:03:04.210 --> 01:03:06.210
There's no pain would prise his need from him.

923
01:03:07.720 --> 01:03:09.720
A lot of guys think that.

924
01:03:09.720 --> 01:03:11.220
until the pain starts.

925
01:03:13.640 --> 01:03:15.140
What are you asking me to do?

926
01:03:15.140 --> 01:03:18.810
I'm asking. what are you prepared to do?

927
01:03:18.810 --> 01:03:19.980
Loki is a prisoner.

928
01:03:19.980 --> 01:03:20.900
Then why do I feel like

929
01:03:21.400 --> 01:03:22.400
he's the only person on this boat

930
01:03:22.400 --> 01:03:24.150
that wants to be here?

931
01:03:36.860 --> 01:03:39.860
There's not many people who can sneak up on me.

932
01:03:39.870 --> 01:03:41.680
But you figured I'd come.

933
01:03:42.450 --> 01:03:44.700
After.

934
01:03:44.700 --> 01:03:48.210
After whatever tortures Fury can concoct.

935
01:03:48.210 --> 01:03:52.210
you would appear as a friend. as a balm.

936
01:03:52.710 --> 01:03:54.510
And I would cooperate.

937
01:03:54.930 --> 01:03:57.050
I want to know what you've done to Agent Barton.

938
01:03:57.050 --> 01:03:58.850
I would say I've expanded his mind.

939
01:04:01.640 --> 01:04:04.140
And once you've won.

940
01:04:04.140 --> 01:04:06.860
once you're king of the mountain.

941
01:04:07.860 --> 01:04:10.140
what happens to his mind?

942
01:04:10.150 --> 01:04:11.620
Oh...

943
01:04:11.610 --> 01:04:13.560
Is this love. Agent Romanoff?

944
01:04:13.570 --> 01:04:16.080
Love is for children. I owe him a debt.

945
01:04:19.990 --> 01:04:21.490
Tell me.

946
01:04:26.250 --> 01:04:29.760
Before I worked for S.H.I.E.L.D.. I. uh...

947
01:04:31.750 --> 01:04:35.750
Well. I made a name for myself.

948
01:04:35.760 --> 01:04:39.270
I have a very specific skill set.

949
01:04:39.260 --> 01:04:43.560
I didn't care who I used it for. or on.

950
01:04:43.560 --> 01:04:47.320
I got on S.H.I.E.L.D.'s radar in a bad way.

951
01:04:48.600 --> 01:04:51.600
Agent Barton was sent to kill me.

952
01:04:52.610 --> 01:04:53.920
He made a different call.

953
01:04:55.780 --> 01:04:59.250
And what will you do if I vow to spare him?

954
01:04:59.250 --> 01:05:00.590
Not let you out.

955
01:05:00.580 --> 01:05:03.530
No. but I like this.

956
01:05:03.530 --> 01:05:06.920
Your world in the balance. and you bargain for one man.

957
01:05:06.920 --> 01:05:09.370
Regimes fall every day.

958
01:05:09.370 --> 01:05:11.870
I tend not to weep over that. I'm Russian.

959
01:05:11.870 --> 01:05:12.870
Or I was.

960
01:05:14.290 --> 01:05:16.290
And what are you now?

961
01:05:16.300 --> 01:05:19.310
It's really not that complicated.

962
01:05:19.300 --> 01:05:23.800
I got red in my ledger. I'd like to wipe it out.

963
01:05:24.800 --> 01:05:26.100
Can you?

964
01:05:27.470 --> 01:05:31.480
Can you wipe out that much red?

965
01:05:32.480 --> 01:05:34.230
Dreykov's daughter.

966
01:05:35.530 --> 01:05:37.530
Sao Paulo.

967
01:05:38.530 --> 01:05:40.900
the hospital fire?

968
01:05:41.870 --> 01:05:44.370
Barton told me everything.

969
01:05:44.370 --> 01:05:47.380
Your ledger is dripping. It's gushing red.

970
01:05:47.380 --> 01:05:48.830
and you think saving a man

971
01:05:48.830 --> 01:05:50.330
no more virtuous than yourself

972
01:05:50.330 --> 01:05:51.830
will change anything?

973
01:05:51.830 --> 01:05:54.330
This is the basest sentimentality.

974
01:05:54.330 --> 01:05:56.830
This is a child at prayer.

975
01:05:56.840 --> 01:05:58.150
Pathetic!

976
01:05:59.000 --> 01:06:01.510
<i>You lie and kill</i>

977
01:06:01.510 --> 01:06:04.430
<i>in the service of liars and killers.</i>

978
01:06:07.930 --> 01:06:11.350
<i>You pretend to be separate. to have your own code.</i>

979
01:06:11.350 --> 01:06:13.850
<i>something that makes up for the horrors.</i>

980
01:06:14.850 --> 01:06:17.360
<i>But they are part of you.</i>

981
01:06:17.360 --> 01:06:21.660
<i>And they will never go away.</i>

982
01:06:22.160 --> 01:06:25.280
I won't touch Barton. not until I make him kill you.

983
01:06:25.280 --> 01:06:27.780
Slowly. intimately.

984
01:06:27.780 --> 01:06:30.530
in every way he knows you fear.

985
01:06:30.540 --> 01:06:33.350
And then he'll wake just long enough to see his good work.

986
01:06:33.840 --> 01:06:37.340
and when he screams. I'll split his skull.

987
01:06:37.340 --> 01:06:40.180
This is my bargain. you mewling quim.

988
01:06:42.130 --> 01:06:43.630
You're a monster.

989
01:06:45.800 --> 01:06:47.300
Oh. no.

990
01:06:48.300 --> 01:06:49.600
You brought the monster.

991
01:06:52.530 --> 01:06:54.320
So. Banner.

992
01:06:55.110 --> 01:06:56.440
That's your play.

993
01:06:56.450 --> 01:06:57.710
What?

994
01:06:58.480 --> 01:07:00.200
Loki means to unleash the Hulk.

995
01:07:00.200 --> 01:07:01.980
Keep Banner in the lab. I'm on my way.

996
01:07:01.980 --> 01:07:03.030
Send Thor as well.

997
01:07:04.900 --> 01:07:06.150
Thank you

998
01:07:06.160 --> 01:07:08.470
for your cooperation.

999
01:07:15.970 --> 01:07:17.480
What are you doing. Mr. Stark?

1000
01:07:17.470 --> 01:07:20.330
Uh. kind of been wondering the same thing about you.

1001
01:07:20.340 --> 01:07:21.810
You're supposed to be locating the Tesseract.

1002
01:07:22.300 --> 01:07:23.590
We are. The model's locked

1003
01:07:23.590 --> 01:07:25.010
and we're sweeping for the signature now.

1004
01:07:25.010 --> 01:07:26.510
When we get a hit.

1005
01:07:26.510 --> 01:07:28.260
we'll have the location within half a mile.

1006
01:07:28.640 --> 01:07:32.760
Yeah. then you get your Cube back. No muss. no fuss.

1007
01:07:32.770 --> 01:07:33.770
What is "Phase 2"?

1008
01:07:36.270 --> 01:07:38.940
Phase 2 is S.H.I.E.L.D. uses the Cube to make weapons.

1009
01:07:38.940 --> 01:07:41.270
Sorry. computer was moving a little slow for me.

1010
01:07:41.270 --> 01:07:43.690
Rogers. we gathered everything related to the Tesseract.

1011
01:07:43.690 --> 01:07:45.190
This does not mean that we're making...

1012
01:07:45.190 --> 01:07:46.410
I'm sorry. Nick.

1013
01:07:46.410 --> 01:07:48.780
What were you lying?

1014
01:07:48.780 --> 01:07:50.030
I was wrong. Director.

1015
01:07:50.030 --> 01:07:51.500
The world hasn't changed a bit.

1016
01:07:51.780 --> 01:07:52.530
Did you know about this?

1017
01:07:52.870 --> 01:07:53.870
You want to think about removing yourself

1018
01:07:54.370 --> 01:07:55.790
from this environment. Doctor?

1019
01:07:55.790 --> 01:07:57.670
I was in Calcutta. I was pretty well removed.

1020
01:07:57.670 --> 01:07:59.120
Loki is manipulating you.

1021
01:07:59.430 --> 01:08:00.680
And you've been doing what. exactly?

1022
01:08:00.680 --> 01:08:02.470
You didn't come here because I bat my eyelashes at you.

1023
01:08:02.460 --> 01:08:03.930
Yes. and I'm not leaving

1024
01:08:03.930 --> 01:08:05.430
because suddenly you get a little twitchy.

1025
01:08:05.430 --> 01:08:06.930
I'd like to know why S.H.I.E.L.D.

1026
01:08:06.930 --> 01:08:08.430
is using the Tesseract

1027
01:08:08.430 --> 01:08:10.770
to build weapons of mass destruction.

1028
01:08:11.640 --> 01:08:12.520
Because of him.

1029
01:08:14.020 --> 01:08:15.610
Me?

1030
01:08:15.610 --> 01:08:18.230
Last year. Earth had a visitor from another planet

1031
01:08:18.230 --> 01:08:21.400
who had a grudge match that leveled a small town.

1032
01:08:21.900 --> 01:08:23.730
We learned that not only are we not alone.

1033
01:08:23.730 --> 01:08:27.700
but we are hopelessly. hilariously. outgunned.

1034
01:08:27.700 --> 01:08:29.950
My people want nothing but peace with your planet.

1035
01:08:29.960 --> 01:08:32.250
But you're not the only people out there. are you?

1036
01:08:32.240 --> 01:08:34.460
And you're not the only threat.

1037
01:08:34.460 --> 01:08:38.210
The world's filling up with people who can't be matched.

1038
01:08:38.210 --> 01:08:39.210
that can't be controlled.

1039
01:08:39.670 --> 01:08:40.670
Like you controlled the Cube?

1040
01:08:40.670 --> 01:08:41.890
Your work with the Tesseract

1041
01:08:41.880 --> 01:08:44.890
is what drew Loki to it. and his allies.

1042
01:08:44.890 --> 01:08:46.390
It is a signal to all the realms

1043
01:08:46.390 --> 01:08:48.890
that the Earth is ready for a higher form of war.

1044
01:08:48.890 --> 01:08:50.390
A higher form?

1045
01:08:50.390 --> 01:08:51.390
You forced our hand.

1046
01:08:51.390 --> 01:08:52.390
We had to come up with something.

1047
01:08:52.390 --> 01:08:53.890
A nuclear deterrent.

1048
01:08:53.900 --> 01:08:55.910
Because that always calms everything right down.

1049
01:08:55.900 --> 01:08:58.400
Remind me again how you made your fortune. Stark.

1050
01:08:58.400 --> 01:08:59.400
I'm sure if he still made weapons.

1051
01:08:59.400 --> 01:09:00.650
Stark would be neck-deep...

1052
01:09:00.650 --> 01:09:02.490
Hold on. How is this now about me?

1053
01:09:02.490 --> 01:09:03.490
I'm sorry. isn't everything?

1054
01:09:03.990 --> 01:09:05.490
I thought humans were more evolved than this.

1055
01:09:05.990 --> 01:09:08.490
Excuse me. did we come to your planet and blow stuff up?

1056
01:09:08.990 --> 01:09:10.490
You treat your champions with such mistrust.

1057
01:09:11.000 --> 01:09:12.500
Are you boys really that naive?

1058
01:09:12.500 --> 01:09:14.500
S.H.I.E.L.D. monitors potential threats.

1059
01:09:14.500 --> 01:09:15.500
Captain America's on threat watch?

1060
01:09:16.000 --> 01:09:17.000
We all are.

1061
01:09:17.000 --> 01:09:18.500
Wait. you're on that list?

1062
01:09:18.500 --> 01:09:20.290
Are you above or below angry bees?

1063
01:09:20.290 --> 01:09:21.120
Stark. so help me God.

1064
01:09:21.120 --> 01:09:22.620
if you make one more wisecrack...

1065
01:09:22.620 --> 01:09:23.620
Threat! Verbal threat. I feel threatened.

1066
01:09:23.630 --> 01:09:25.640
- Show some respect. - Respect what?

1067
01:09:33.640 --> 01:09:35.280
<i>Transport Six-Six-Bravo.</i>

1068
01:09:35.270 --> 01:09:36.600
<i>please relay confirm codes.</i>

1069
01:09:36.610 --> 01:09:39.120
<i>I've got you on the computer. but not on the day log.</i>

1070
01:09:39.110 --> 01:09:41.110
<i>What is your haul? Over.</i>

1071
01:09:41.110 --> 01:09:43.610
Arms and  ammunition. Over.

1072
01:09:51.900 --> 01:09:54.320
You speak of control. yet you court chaos.

1073
01:09:54.320 --> 01:09:56.070
That's his M.O.. isn't it?

1074
01:09:56.080 --> 01:09:57.500
I mean. what are we. a team?

1075
01:09:57.490 --> 01:10:00.490
No. we're a chemical mixture that makes chaos.

1076
01:10:01.000 --> 01:10:02.500
We're a time bomb.

1077
01:10:02.500 --> 01:10:04.500
You need to step away.

1078
01:10:05.000 --> 01:10:06.470
Why shouldn't the guy let off a little steam?

1079
01:10:06.970 --> 01:10:08.970
You know damn well why. Back off!

1080
01:10:08.970 --> 01:10:11.470
I'm starting to want you to make me.

1081
01:10:11.470 --> 01:10:14.840
Yeah. Big man in a suit of armor.

1082
01:10:14.840 --> 01:10:16.840
Take that off. what are you?

1083
01:10:16.850 --> 01:10:19.820
Genius. billionaire. playboy. philanthropist.

1084
01:10:19.820 --> 01:10:23.190
I know guys with none of that worth ten of you.

1085
01:10:23.190 --> 01:10:24.500
I've seen the footage.

1086
01:10:24.490 --> 01:10:26.350
The only thing you really fight for is yourself.

1087
01:10:27.740 --> 01:10:29.940
You're not the guy to make the sacrifice play.

1088
01:10:30.280 --> 01:10:32.590
to lay down on a wire and let the other guy crawl over you.

1089
01:10:32.910 --> 01:10:34.750
I think I would just cut the wire.

1090
01:10:38.120 --> 01:10:39.620
Always a way out.

1091
01:10:39.620 --> 01:10:41.120
You may not be a threat.

1092
01:10:41.120 --> 01:10:43.370
but you better stop pretending to be a hero.

1093
01:10:43.370 --> 01:10:45.870
A hero? Like you?

1094
01:10:45.870 --> 01:10:47.880
You're a laboratory experiment. Rogers.

1095
01:10:47.880 --> 01:10:51.380
Everything special about you came out of a bottle.

1096
01:11:16.660 --> 01:11:18.880
Put on the suit. Let's go a few rounds.

1097
01:11:20.460 --> 01:11:24.410
You people are so petty. and tiny.

1098
01:11:24.410 --> 01:11:25.330
Yeah. this is a team.

1099
01:11:25.330 --> 01:11:26.830
Agent Romanoff. would you escort

1100
01:11:26.830 --> 01:11:27.720
Dr. Banner back to his...

1101
01:11:27.720 --> 01:11:29.550
Where? You rented my room.

1102
01:11:30.000 --> 01:11:31.500
The cell was just in case...

1103
01:11:31.500 --> 01:11:32.970
In case you needed to kill me.

1104
01:11:32.970 --> 01:11:35.810
But you can't. I know. I tried.

1105
01:11:38.560 --> 01:11:41.560
I got low. I didn't see an end.

1106
01:11:41.560 --> 01:11:43.560
So. I put a bullet in my mouth.

1107
01:11:43.570 --> 01:11:46.580
and the other guy spit it out.

1108
01:11:47.070 --> 01:11:48.070
So I moved on.

1109
01:11:48.070 --> 01:11:50.850
I focused on helping other people. I was good.

1110
01:11:50.860 --> 01:11:53.170
Until you dragged me back into this freak show

1111
01:11:53.160 --> 01:11:54.660
and put everyone here at risk.

1112
01:11:55.110 --> 01:11:57.110
You want to know my secret. Agent Romanoff?

1113
01:11:57.110 --> 01:11:58.910
You want to know how I stay calm?

1114
01:12:01.580 --> 01:12:03.830
Dr. Banner.

1115
01:12:04.790 --> 01:12:06.040
put down the scepter.

1116
01:12:14.680 --> 01:12:16.180
Got it.

1117
01:12:16.680 --> 01:12:18.180
Sorry. kids.

1118
01:12:18.180 --> 01:12:19.680
you don't get to see my party trick after all.

1119
01:12:19.690 --> 01:12:20.690
You located the Tesseract?

1120
01:12:21.190 --> 01:12:21.970
I could get there fastest.

1121
01:12:21.970 --> 01:12:23.270
The Tesseract belongs on Asgard.

1122
01:12:23.270 --> 01:12:24.560
No human is a match for it.

1123
01:12:24.560 --> 01:12:25.560
You're not going alone.         You're gonna stop me?

1124
01:12:25.560 --> 01:12:26.560
Put on the suit. let's find out.

1125
01:12:27.030 --> 01:12:28.540
I'm not afraid to hit an old man.

1126
01:12:28.530 --> 01:12:29.310
Put on the suit.

1127
01:12:32.200 --> 01:12:33.700
Oh. my God.

1128
01:12:49.630 --> 01:12:50.630
Put on the suit.

1129
01:12:50.630 --> 01:12:51.630
Yeah.

1130
01:12:54.800 --> 01:12:56.140
<i>All hands to stations.</i>

1131
01:13:00.230 --> 01:13:02.100
-               Hill! - External detonation.

1132
01:13:02.090 --> 01:13:03.560
Number three engine is down.

1133
01:13:03.560 --> 01:13:05.060
We've been hit.

1134
01:13:05.060 --> 01:13:06.060
-      Can they get it running? - Fire in engine three!

1135
01:13:06.060 --> 01:13:07.060
Talk to me.

1136
01:13:07.070 --> 01:13:09.080
Turbine looks mostly intact.

1137
01:13:09.070 --> 01:13:11.070
but it's impossible to get out there to make repairs

1138
01:13:11.070 --> 01:13:12.570
while we're in the air.

1139
01:13:12.570 --> 01:13:15.070
If we lose one more engine. we won't be.

1140
01:13:15.070 --> 01:13:17.160
Somebody's got to get outside and patch that engine.

1141
01:13:17.160 --> 01:13:18.990
-   Stark. you copy that? - I'm on it.

1142
01:13:18.990 --> 01:13:21.410
<i>Coulson. initiate defensive lockdown</i>

1143
01:13:21.410 --> 01:13:22.410
<i>in the detention section.</i>

1144
01:13:22.410 --> 01:13:23.660
<i>then get to the armory.</i>

1145
01:13:23.670 --> 01:13:24.790
Romanoff?

1146
01:13:28.290 --> 01:13:29.790
We're okay.

1147
01:13:32.760 --> 01:13:33.620
We're okay. right?

1148
01:13:46.220 --> 01:13:47.690
Keep that engine down!              Yes. sir.

1149
01:13:47.690 --> 01:13:49.690
Detention. wait for cameras to go dark.

1150
01:13:49.690 --> 01:13:51.190
Got it. Stay close.

1151
01:13:53.360 --> 01:13:55.280
Let's go. Level 4.

1152
01:13:55.280 --> 01:13:57.700
Engine three. I'll meet you there.

1153
01:14:06.290 --> 01:14:07.790
Doctor?

1154
01:14:10.050 --> 01:14:11.310
Bruce?

1155
01:14:11.300 --> 01:14:15.050
You got to fight it. This is just what Loki wants.

1156
01:14:16.340 --> 01:14:17.340
We're going to be okay. Listen to me.

1157
01:14:17.840 --> 01:14:18.340
Are you hurt?

1158
01:14:22.060 --> 01:14:24.390
We're going to be okay. All right?

1159
01:14:24.390 --> 01:14:27.260
I swear on my life. I will get you out of this.

1160
01:14:27.260 --> 01:14:28.730
You will walk away and never ever...

1161
01:14:28.730 --> 01:14:30.510
Your life?

1162
01:14:47.170 --> 01:14:48.040
Bruce.
